      <title>Stop Waiting for “Junior” Roles: AI Ate the First Rung</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/stop-waiting-for-junior-roles/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 07 Sep 2025 08:30:00 +0530</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/stop-waiting-for-junior-roles/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure class=&#34;responsive-image&#34; style=&#34;margin: 2rem 0; text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture&gt;&#xA;      &lt;source media=&#34;(max-width: 600px)&#34; srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/stop-waiting-for-junior-roles/images/thumbnail_hu_290c499da56889a8.png&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;source media=&#34;(max-width: 900px)&#34; srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/stop-waiting-for-junior-roles/images/thumbnail_hu_1e277159f404b510.png&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/stop-waiting-for-junior-roles/images/thumbnail_hu_99c11ae0f11bf1af.png&#34; &#xA;           alt=&#34;Experience required for Junior level: 5 years&#34; &#xA;           loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xA;           style=&#34;max-width: 100%; height: auto; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);&#34;&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&lt;figcaption style=&#34;margin-top: 1rem; font-style: italic; color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem;&#34;&gt;Exp required for Junior level : 5 years&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-empty-mall-effect&#34;&gt;The Empty Mall Effect&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open your favorite job board. Notice the silence? It feels like wandering an abandoned mall: the food court is still lit, a couple of anchor stores survive, but the ground floor, the kiosks, the first rung, is empty. Not because tech collapsed. Because the roles that used to teach beginners were the easiest to automate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
